Chocolate Cake Day: January 27,United States,1,27,2021,1,27,2021,19,52,,,, ,Daily,Same,,https://www.theodysseyonline.com/8-reasons-national-chocolate-cake-day-day,,,About National Chocolate Cake Day,,"Love chocolate cake? Then you have James Baker to thanks. 

Baker invented chocolate as we know it today, that is, in a form that could easily be cooked.  In 1764 Mr. Baker placed beans between millstones and ground them down to dust.  This powder could then be mixed with liquids or solids to change the flavor, the same way you add salt or other seasonings.  However, this process was quite expensive, so only the wealthiest people could afford it.  By the early nineteenth century (1828) Conrad Van Houten developed a method for extracting the cacao liquor from the fat in the cocoa bean.  This made chocolate an affordable ingredient and its popularity took off. 

Devil’s Food cake by the Pittsburgh based Duff Company was the first chocolate cake mix. However, WWII got in the way and at the end of the war Duncan Hines and General Mills burst on the scene with their mixes and took nearly half the market between them. 

By the millennium, artisan chocolate cakes, those without flour and closer to the consistency of fudge brownies with less sugar became the rage. 

However you like your chocolate cake, today is the day to enjoy it.  Indulge!",Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.  See Cordon Bleu Culinary School for info,Cordon Bleu,8 Rue Léon Delhomme,Paris,,FR,75015,(+33)(1) 53.68.22.50,mwarren@cordonbleu.edu,Media Relations,http://www.cordonbleuusa.com/,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
"Chocolate Covered Cherry Day, Ntl.: January 3",United States,1,3,2021,1,3,2021,19,52,,,, ,Daily,Same,,https://www.candyfavorites.com/blog/a-history-of-cherry-cordials-for-valentines-day/,,,About National Chocolate Covered Cherry Day,,"Chocolate Covered Cherry Day celebrates the cordial of cherries covered in chocolate.

The idea of covering fruits, nuts and even nougat with chocolate wasn’t really possible until the 19th Century. The technology needed to separate the chocolate from cocoa butter wouldn’t be invented until 1828 by Conrad Van Houten in today’s Netherlands. Without this process, chocolate could only be used as a spice, much the same way you would use cinnamon or ginger.

Fortunately, the process was developed and further techniques, including conching, invented by Rudolph Lindt in 1879 would eventually lead to that box of chocolates everyone loves to get. 

Chocolate Covered Cherry Day is an unofficial holiday with no sponsor.",Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See Fine Chocolate Industry Association for info/details,Fine Chocolate Industry Association,4701 SW Admiral Way #324,Seattle,WA,US,98116,(206) 577.9983,info@finechocolateindustry.org,Media Relations,http://www.finechocolateindustry.org/ballyhoo,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
"Christian Unity Week, Intl. (Northern Hemisphere): January 18-25",Northern Hemisphere,1,18,2021,1,25,2021,3,10,38,,,,Weekly,Same,Feast of Saint Peter and the conversion of Saint Paul.,http://www.oikoumene.org/en/press-centre/events/week-of-prayer-for-christian-unity,,,About International Christian Unity Week,,"At least once a year (January in the Northern Hemisphere, June in the Southern Hemisphere), Christians are reminded of Jesus’ prayer for his disciples that “they may be one so that the world may believe” (see John 17.21). Hearts are touched and Christians come together to pray for their unity. Congregations and parishes all over the world exchange preachers or arrange special ecumenical celebrations and prayer services. The event that touches off this special experience is the Week of Prayer for Christian Unity.

Traditionally the week of prayer is celebrated between 18-25 January, between the feasts of St Peter and St Paul. In the southern hemisphere, where January is a vacation time, churches often find other days to celebrate it, for example around Pentecost, which is also a symbolic date for unity.",World Council of Churches,Ecumenical Centre,1 Route des Morillons,Le Grand-Saconnex , ,CH,1218,(+41) 79 507.6363,mej@wcc-coe.org,"Marianne Ejdersten, WCC Communications Director ",http://ncca.org/contact-us.aspx,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
