"Holocaust Victims' Day, World (1945): January 27",Worldwide,1,27,2021,1,27,2021,3,29,59,16,,,Daily,Same,,http://www.un.org/en/holocaustremembrance/2018/calendar2018.html,,,About World Holocaust Victims' Day,,"Holocaust Victims' Day remembers the horrific events which began in 1942. The day marks the liberation of Auschwitz concentration camp by Russian soldiers on January 27, 1945. 

The Holocaust is one of the most significant tragedies in recent history - both in scale and in the mark it left on humanity. People were targeted due to their faith, physical and/or mental challenges, political views, color and sexual orientation, imprisoned and in many cases murdered or starved to death.  People targeted by the Nazi regime for imprisonment and extermination included those of the Jewish faith, Catholic faith, Romani (Gypsies), Mentally Ill, Handicap, Communists, Persons of color and Homosexuals. 

The largest single group targeted and murdered were those of the Jewish faith, representing  25% of the world’s Jewish population. Though a much smaller worldwide population, 25% of the world’s Romani population were also exterminated during the Holocaust. 

This day is set aside each year to remember all the victims, regardless of faith, race, health or sexual orientation, as well as the circumstances leading up to and causing this international tragedy.",United Nations,Palais des Nation,,Geneva , ,CH,1211,(212) 963.7160,contactnewscentre@un.org,Media Relations,http://www.un.org/apps/news/html/contactus.asp,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
"Holy Year, Jubilee (C)(ES): 2021",Worldwide,1,1,2021,12,31,2021,10,48,16,,,,Annual,Changes,Years when 7/25 is a Sunday. Next is 2027.,https://oficinadelperegrino.com/en/pilgrimage/holy-year/,HolyYearF.png,HolyYearE.png,About the Holy Year and Jubilee,,"When the Feast of St. James (July 25) falls on a Sunday, that year is celebrated as a Holy Year and a year of Jubilee. The custom began with a Papel Bull issued by Pope Alexander III in 1179. It is believed in Roman Catholic christianity that if one visits the shrine of the apostle during this year, punishment for their sins will be cleansed. It is referred to as plenary indulgence.

Therefore, in holy years, the Cathedral of Santiago sees a significant increase in religious pilgrims. They enter through the 'Holy Door'. Access to this significant entrance is only available during Holy Years. Image: Jl FilpoC, CC BY-SA 4.0 <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0>, via Wikimedia Commons ",Cathedral of Santiago,"Rúa Carretas, nº33",15705 Santiago de Compostela,A Coruña,,ES,,(+34) 981.568.846,oficinadelperegrino@catedraldesantiago.es,General  Information,https://oficinadelperegrino.com/en/pilgrimage/holy-year/,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
