Hot Pastrami Sandwich Day: January 14,United States,1,14,2021,1,14,2021,19,52,,,,,Daily,Same,,https://www.sandwichtribunal.com/2018/01/national-hot-pastrami-sandwich-day/,,,About Hot Pastrami Sandwich Day,,"Hot Pastrami Sandwich Day warms up mid-January every year. The name pastrami is Balkan, from the word ‘pastram_’, the origins of which can be trace back through Greek to Turkish. This type of wind-dried beef has been a traditional food in Anatolia for centuries, probably predating the Ottomans.

American pastrami is usually made from the navel end of the brisket. It's cured and coated with a mix of spices such as garlic, coriander, black pepper, paprika, cloves, allspice, and mustard seed. After that, it's smoked and steamed. The hot pastrami sandwich can be traced back to 1887. ",Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
