"Human Trafficking Awareness & Prevention Month, Nt.: January",United States,1,1,2021,1,31,2021,59,8,42,48,51,52,Monthly,Same,,https://www.ecpatusa.org/human-trafficking-prevention-month,,,About National Human Trafficking Awareness & Prevention Month,,"National Human Trafficking Awareness & Prevention Month is an initiative of ECPAT-USA, an association of travel and entertainment companies that seeks to protect every child’s basic human right to grow up free from the threat of sexual exploitation and trafficking.

The primary objectives of this organization and the month are to:

1) Advocate for federal and state legislation that prevents exploitation, protects children, and guarantees that any child who is subjected to sexual slavery or sex trafficking will not be prosecuted in the courts for prostitution.

2) Promote corporate responsibility among private companies with a strong focus on the tourism sector.

3) Educate first responders and ordinary citizens about this issue so that they can identify victims and join us in the fight to better protect children.

4) Empower youth to take the lead against human trafficking by equipping them with the knowledge and tools necessary to help them become activists against this terrible trade.",ECPAT-USA,30 3rd Ave. #800A,,Brooklyn,NY,US,11217,(718) 935.9192,info@ecpatusa.org,General Information,https://www.ecpatusa.org/media-request/,"<iframe width=“640"" height=""360"" src=""https://www.youtube.com/embed/WMk53IkJco8"" frameborder=""0"" allow=""accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"" allowfullscreen></iframe>","<iframe width=“640"" height=“360"" src=""https://www.youtube.com/embed/KllVVJ4seBA"" frameborder=""0"" allow=""accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"" allowfullscreen></iframe>","<iframe width=“640"" height=“360"" src=""https://www.youtube.com/embed/BmmRTjoL3R0"" frameborder=""0"" allow=""accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"" allowfullscreen></iframe>",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
"Human Trafficking, Wear Blue Day: January 11",United States,1,11,2021,1,11,2021,59,8,42,52,,,Daily,Same,,https://www.dhs.gov/blue-campaign,,,About Homeland Security's Blue Campaign to End Human Trafficking,,"The Blue Campaign is the unified voice for the U.S. Department of Homeland Security’s (DHS) efforts to combat human trafficking. Working in collaboration with law enforcement, government, non-governmental and private organizations, the Blue Campaign strives to protect the basic right of freedom and to bring those who exploit human lives to justice.

Through the Blue Campaign, DHS raises public awareness about human trafficking, leveraging partnerships to educate the public to recognize human trafficking and report suspected instances. The Blue Campaign also offers training to law enforcement and others to increase detection and investigation of human trafficking, and to protect victims and bring suspected traffickers to justice. To view all available Blue Campaign resources, please visit our resources page.

DHS is responsible for investigating human trafficking, arresting traffickers, and protecting victims. DHS also provides immigration relief to non-U.S. citizen victims of human trafficking. DHS utilizes a victim-centered approach to combat human trafficking, which places equal value on identifying and stabilizing victims and on investigating and prosecuting traffickers. Victims are crucial to investigations and prosecutions; each case and every conviction changes lives. DHS understands how difficult it can be for victims to come forward and work with law enforcement due to their trauma. DHS is committed to helping victims feel stable, safe, and secure.",Department of Homeland Security,245 Murray Lane SW,,Washington,DC,US,20528-0075,(202) 282.8010,mediainquiry@dhs.gov,Public Affairs,https://www.dhs.gov/media-contacts,"<iframe width=“640"" height=“360"" src=""https://www.youtube.com/embed/BmmRTjoL3R0"" frameborder=""0"" allow=""accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"" allowfullscreen></iframe>",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
