The service no longer exists. 'Honey, can you pick up milk on your way home?' is a familiar request in households. So familiar that supermarkets and convenience stores purposely put milk at the back of their stores hoping people will have impulse purchases as they walk through. One could argue that companies like Fresh Direct and Amazon have become the gig-economy milkmen. 

