"Sticker Day, Ntl (1907): January 13",United States,1,13,2021,1,13,2021,3,22,12,18,39,52,Daily,Same,,https://www.stickergiant.com/national-sticker-day,,,About National Sticker Day,,"Today is the birthday of Ray Stanton Avery, January 13, 1907. Avery invented the first self adhesive labels for pricing, known as the Kum Kleen Pricer Stickers. This single invention grew into the company we know today as Avery Dennison Corporation. From the humble price sticker grew an entire industry of commercial and copyrighted colorful stickers, ranging from gold stars and smiley faces to well known cartoons and characters. National Sticker Day celebrates the contributions of Avery to commerce and popular culture and occurs annually on the day of his birth. Avery died December 12, 1997. ",Historical Anniversary. See Avery Dennison on Topic.,Avery Dennison,207 Goode Ave,Glendale,CA,US,,(626) 304.2000,,Media Relations,https://www.averydennison.com/en/home/newsroom.html,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
