The name of the holiday comes from 'Toad Hollow Country School', a story written by a girl named Eunice in the early 19th century. The story was later picked up by her college professor Ralph C. Morrison. 

Mr. Morrison read and liked the story so much that he incorporated it into his own storytelling and thus a legend was born. Toad Hollow Day of Encouragement is inspired the story’s message of openness and connectedness with people.",Toad Hollow Vineyards,PO BOX 876,,Healdsburg,CA,US,95448,(888) 862.3846,http://www.toadhollow.com/contact,General Information,http://www.toadhollow.com/contact,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LEEP
