The tree-metaphor is fundamental in Judaism which sees trees as a metaphor for people, divided into three parts: roots, then trunk, branches and leaves, and finally, fruit as the third part. 

Each portion of the tree has a metaphoric meaning that corresponds to people's lives, struggles and goals.",Jewish Religious Holiday: See True Torah Jews Ask a Rabbi service ,True Torah Jews,"183 Wilson Street,
